Constraints on the temperature for inner core crystallization can be obtained by examining the thermal stability of Fe4+xS3, which increases quite significantly with pressure, from less than 1200 K at 14 GPa22 to ~1500 K at 21 GPa17. At higher temperatures, Fe4+xS3 will melt incongruently to form solid FeS and Fe-S liquid: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
